The paper discusses learning Restricted Boltzmann Machines (RBMs), which are a popular model in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses tools from mathematical physics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, RBMs have applications in artificial intelligence, which could place the paper in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the representational power of RBMs, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
